laboratory_examinations.findings: Skeletal Class I in a hyperdivergent, biretrused patient with growth pattern of clockwise mandibular rotation.

In the upper arch, central and lateral deciduous incisors are present; permanent counterparts can be seen. Small buds referring to first premolars can be observed; buds of the second premolar and first molar are not visible. Erupted teeth similar to molars with large cubic crowns. Buds of the second and third molars are present. In the lower arch, substantial anterior crowding; lateral incisors are included due to lack of adequate space for eruption. Buds of the premolars and first molars are absent bilaterally; buds of the second and third molars are present distally.
